<br>
Dear Mr. Scotto:<br>
<br>
We are the members of &quot;Vis Veres&quot; (hereinafter &quot;VV&quot;), a player run <br>
guild the Everquest server &quot;Tribunal.&quot; We write to you on <br>
behalf of our guild, which represents approximately 120 players, many of <br>
which pay for multiple TEN WHOLE DOLLAH subscriptions to partake in the experience promised by the Evequest service.<br>
<br>
Through <br>
aggressive cross-server recruitment, promotion, and planning, we insured <br>
that by the time the SOL expansion opened we had a large number of <br>
customers ready and willing to join us. For example, on the day SOL went live, we had approximately two hundred accounts committed <br>
to our guild. The VV guild of today still includes at our <br>
core many of the 200 accounts present on that first day. Our reasons for <br>
dominating this server was to instigate a fresh start and partake in the <br>
promised new content and experiences SOL had to offer.<br>
<br>
Since that day our guild has consistently demonstrated a high level of game <br>
play. Our accomplishments in-game has matched and exceeded that of the top <br>
guilds in Everquest. We very quickly became &quot;the&quot; high profile guild to <br>
measure the success of your service by. And you will note we always <br>
portrayed a positive attitude towards the server, staff and players. Our <br>
site and accomplishments were very quickly picked up and viewed by players <br>
on all servers in Everquest.<br>
<br>
When the inevitable conflicts over spawns with other guilds on Tribunal <br>
began, we have consistently demonstrated a willingness to resolve problems <br>
and issues as suggested by the GMs. For <br>
example, we delayed waking the Sleeper in Sleeper's Tomb for over three <br>
months at the suggestion of the GM Bahlzaq. Additionally, for a <br>
substantial time prior to the institution of a &quot;calendar&quot; system, we <br>
voluntarily avoided spawns more representative of earlier phases of the game <br>
(e.g., North Temple of Veeshan) and devoted our guilds focus to new content <br>
which was not in pursuit or conflict with any other guild entities on the <br>
server. When the &quot;calendar&quot; system was forced upon us, the staff admitted <br>
that spawn conflicts were greatly diminished, primarily due to our voluntary <br>
efforts.<br>
<br>
We quickly became disillusioned with the promises of new content, events, <br>
and ph4t l3wtz that had initially prompted us to Ubarize ourselves. It became painfully obvious that even the Server <br>
GMs were being held hostage by the fact that they didn’t have the content <br>
that was needed to pacify so many high level players on the server.<br>
<br>
Although we did not agree with allowing other guilds to touch our goodies, we did <br>
accept it in order to work with Sony staff and provide a comfortable <br>
community for the server. We also placed our trust in the Customer service <br>
staff when they said “trust us it will be OK”.<br>
<br>
After EV killed the Emperor guy when we wanted to, our guild has reached the <br>
conclusion that a definite and distinct pattern of biased exists against our <br>
guild through repeated acts of the Customer service staff (and principally <br>
through decisions made by GM &quot;Bahlzaq&quot;). In short, the VV Domination Rotation<br>
not being enforced fairly and is currently administered so that it is biased <br>
against VV.<br>
<br>
We have considered this previously and did not take steps then, due to the <br>
repeated assurances from GM &quot;Bahlzaq&quot; that such favoritism would stop and the <br>
inconsistencies would halt. In <br>
direct discussions with Senior GM staff we were assured that certain actions <br>
on the part of the GM’s would be “looked in to” and “addressed”. Time frames <br>
were placed on questionable GM decisions with promises of direct action <br>
items to ensure these occurrences would not happen again. None of this has <br>
happened; in fact the inconstancies have grown in number.<br>
<br>
The incidents which support this bias are too lengthy and numerous <br>
to recite in this letter, however, rest assured they have been documented <br>
and have been submitted in our complaint to the San Diego Better Business <br>
Bureau, whom we've been informed has on previous occasion dealt with nearly <br>
100 cases against SOE.<br>
<br>
<br>
Notice<br>
<br>
Given the current environment on the Tribunal server, the bias <br>
demonstrated by the staff, and our inability to amicably resolve these <br>
issues through the normal customer service process, SOE is hereby placed on <br>
notice that Vis Veres henceforth declares a policy of No Mercy.  LET THE REIGN OF TERROR BEGIN BITCHES! As <br>
of July 24th, 2002 Vis Veres will Systematically gank every spawn on the erver, including Fippy Motherfucking Darkpaw.<br>
<br>
This decision has been made with great sadness. Each one of Vis Veres's accounts represent players who have dedicated enormous time, <br>
energy and money into SOE's Everquest game. Many of our players have over <br>
one year of Everquest play time. Many of our players have been involved with <br>
Everquest since the beta test. In short, we take our gaming experience in <br>
Everquest seriously. Which is why are taking such extreme measures in light <br>
of the waste of our time and money.<br>
<br>
SOE should also recognize that if the Tribunal staff <br>
takes arbitrary retaliatory action against our players/accounts, as we are <br>
most certain GM &quot;Bahlzaq&quot; will condone and attempt to influence us with, we <br>
would consider such actions as a serious matter. Any such action will be <br>
documented, internally reviewed, and publicized if found to be arbitrary or <br>
capricious. In this regard please understand that VV's web site receives <br>
over 10,000 hits daily from Everquest subscribers and we have reached <br>
agreement with other top-tier (i.e., endgame capable) guilds and <br>
guildleaders (e.g., www.fohguild.org &quot;Furor&quot;) in <br>
Everquest for the use of their web space for additional publicity as well as <br>
popular Everquest message boards.<br>
<br>
In closing,<br>
<br>
We are quite unhappy with the situation on Tribunal. We came here under <br>
the premise of phat phreaking lewtz only to have some upstart shitmongering guilds (what the fuck is a Companion?) come on here thinking they can be badasses.<br>
<br>
We feel in its current state it, we will never be <br>
treated with un-bias toward our guild. If another lead customer service GM <br>
can be assigned in replacement of GM &quot;Bahlzaq&quot; perhaps we can move forward.<br>
<br>
Our goal is not to cause problems for any player or staff member. We simply <br>
wish to play the game we have grown to love over the last nearly four years. <br>
Should the server staff wish to continue with its change in policy and <br>
attempt to let these goofy shits share our Uberness, VV is willing to consider relocation to <br>
another server, under certain circumstances. <br>
<br>
VV feels some what held <br>
hostage here on Tribunal and is willing to consider relocation, en mass, <br>
to another Everquest server, so long as that server:<br>
<br>
(1) Does not have an existing &quot;end game&quot; guild;<br>
(2) Is a server not specifically marketed to non-Americans (IE. FUCKING FOREIGNERS!)<br>
(3) Players may transfer with all their equipment and skills intact; and<br>
(4) Any VV member who is willing to make the transfer can take advantage of <br>
the transfer.<br>
(5) The server is not subject to a newly created or imposed GM calendar <br>
system or restraints outside the normal play policy in any way.<br>
<br>
If SOE would be willing to entertain such a transfer, please contact us, you <br>
will find us most cooperative.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind we are happy to stay on the Tribunal server and continue <br>
playing as was our intent. However as <br>
stated we will not be doing so under the cruel sharing rules imposed by the <br>
server staff. Otherwise we are happy to discuss the above solution as a <br>
win/win for everyone.<br>
<br>
Again, it is in no way our intention to cause friction, problems, or <br>
instigate any conflicts on the server. We simply wish to play the game.<br>
<br>
<br>
Yours truly,<br>
<br>
Vis Veres<br>
<br>
<br>
Bowynn<br>
Qaeen<br>
Crush<br>
Mojak<br>
Muse<br>
Rynnia<br>
etc<br>
